Thank you for your message.
There is no limitation regarding retake attempts. However, please note that you have to meet the study progress requirements in order to be able to continue your studies. In Master’s programs, the following number of credits must be achieved:
- a minimum of 30 credits by the end of the third semester;
- a minimum of 60 credits by the end of the fourth semester;
- a minimum of 90 credits by the end of the fifth semester;
- a minimum of 120 credits by the end of the sixth semester.

(2) At least one of the module examinations from the core modules listed in Appendix 1 II must be successfully completed by the end of the second semester.
If you have any other questions, don’t hesitate to contact us.
Best regards,

